snippet: Birdsong, more anxious than chipper, permeated four concerts by the International Contemporary Ensemble that were part of the Mostly Mozart Festival.
abstract: Zachary Woolfe reviews performances by the International Contemporary Ensemble and the Ebene Quartet as part of the Mostly Mozart Festival.
lead_paragraph: Birdsong, more anxious than chipper, permeated four concerts by the International Contemporary Ensemble that were part of the Mostly Mozart Festival.
